<br>
I was reading thru this post and wanted to point out some inconsistencies that stood out to me. I wont touch on the initial camp check because I am sure that if you read the entire post you understood that CoN informed SoY that Vindi was already taken. The points that I don¡¯t want to touch on are:<br>
<br>
1. The idea that was stated about no conversation between SoY and CoN prior to the /ooc that was done while both guilds were in arena area. I ran into some logs statements that disprove this. The logs showed that SoY was told again that CoN was there to take out Vindi. These logs looked like they where from the time frame in-between SoY initial zone in till the setup in Arena area. (Key phrases are in Bold for easy of reading)<br>
<br>
[Mon Nov 04 21:17:02 2002] Perch tells the guild, 'lot of shadows of yamabushi here'<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>[Mon Nov 04 21:17:16 2002] Seanus tells the guild, 'they were asking about vindi... told him he's ours'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
2. The idea that was stated that SoY did not pressure CoN into pulling early, but rather backed off immediately and let them have a shot. The logs I found in the post that show that SoY did in fact pressure CoN into pulling early by stating that they where going to pull Vindi even after Kenshiiro ( GL - SoY I presume ) publicly acknowledged in /ooc the fact that CoN also had an interest in Vindi. *Note: I stated acknowledged that they had an interest in vindi not acknowledged they had a claim*.  By the logs posted, Kenshiiro did indeed blow CoN off without trying to figure out what was going on and stated 'we are Pulling Vindi through Right arena ina few secs...just watch out'   To a reasonable person, this would suggest that SoY was not going to try and work out an arrangement or ( as it was stated repeatedly in previous post) back off immediately and let CoN have a shot. If it would have been me, I would have also felt like SoY were about to steamroll me. Logs that I formed this opinion from are below. *Please also not that the below logs were taken from a different local client than the above. The client used above seems to be in a time zone that is one hour ahead of the client used below.<br>
<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:58:26 2002] Adjutant Hoggren goes on a RAMPAGE!<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:58:27 2002] That is not a valid command. Please use /help.<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:58:28 2002] Sekhar says out of character, 'negative'<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:58:30 2002] Seanus says out of character, 'WHAT!'<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>[Mon Nov 04 20:58:45 2002] Kenshiiro says out of character, '?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:58:59 2002] The mystic symbol fades.<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:59:10 2002] Seanus tells conkael:2, 'Vindi incoming soon folks'<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>[Mon Nov 04 20:59:20 2002] Kenshiiro says out of character, 'CoN?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:59:22 2002] Sekhar tells conkael:2, 'PEOPLE GET READY - I'M GOING TO HAVE TO PULL WHEN I SEE VINDI'<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:59:26 2002] Falden says out of character, 'what?'<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>[Mon Nov 04 20:59:31 2002] Kenshiiro says out of character, 'lol'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:59:45 2002] Adiarea tells the group, 'you ready dear?'<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:59:53 2002] Sekhar tells conkael:2, 'STATUS PLEASE'<br>
[Mon Nov 04 20:59:56 2002] Grymreapz says out of character, 'hey man...have some respect &gt;8p '<br>
[Mon Nov 04 21:00:00 2002] Grymreapz says out of character, ' '<br>
[Mon Nov 04 21:00:01 2002] Aaldawen tells the guild, 'yama is gonna pull vindi '<br>
[Mon Nov 04 21:00:02 2002] Skyewolfe tells conkael:2, 'G4 gtg'<br>
[Mon Nov 04 21:00:03 2002] Lolaorn tells the guild, 'CH ROT gtg'<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>[Mon Nov 04 21:00:03 2002] Kenshiiro says out of character, 'we are Pulling Vindi through Right arena ina few secs...just watch out'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Please note the statements  Kenshiiro makes in the first few posts acknowledging the fact that CoN was also in zone for vindi. Then in the last statement he goes ahead and disregards CoN and gives a warning that SoY is pulling Vindi and to &quot;just watch out&quot;.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that maybe there was some misunderstanding to begin with between CoN and SoY as a guilds, although select individuals in SoY where fully aware of what was going on and either failed their guild by not informing the proper officers of CoN presence and intent or blatantly disregarded CoN all together. I draw this conclusion from the initial camp check done by a SoY member before the rest of SoY even zoned in. Also by the log post that Seanus ( CoN ) stated in guild chat that he had informed SoY that they were there for vindi, prior to SoY being fully mobilized inside the Arena area.<br>
<br>
It also seems to me that SoY, either by being neglectant or lack of consideration, did in fact publicly ( /ooc ) pressure CoN into pulling before they where prepared.<br>
<br>
P.S. I do not know or associate with anyone from either CoN or SoY, but dislike the Rathe community forming opinions about players or guilds without fully looking into what facts where presented to them. I also freely submit the fact that all these opinions where formed from what facts that were presented by CoN logs and that so far I have seen no logs for SoY to dispute them.<br>
